name: Don't Go There
description:
It's past midnight and you see a carousel is still spinning slow.  The lights are shimmering, the somber circus song is blasting through an old megaphone, but nobody is there. Is it for me? Should I come?

The thought of that situation is one of my darkest fears and has been haunting me since I was a kid. But I know it will only happen in movies or whatever. I was wrong. The nightmare finally came true before my very eyes. Honestly there was something melancholic and eerily beautiful about it. But I heard myself telling me, "don't go, don't go there."

Captured with my 2015 ASUS Zenfone 4 - A400CG Android phone and edited on iPhone 7.
